  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Analyzing Visual Elements**\n\nI\'ve begun examining the `src/index.css` file to identify specific visual elements and colors employed in the project. So far, I\'ve noted the presence of the background color `#0b0f19` which is consistently rendered as `bg-[#0b0f19]` and defined as `--color-slate-905`.\n\n\n**Detailing Key Color Choices**\n\nI\'ve made progress in detailing the color scheme, focusing on creating a structured table. I\'ve categorized the colors by role within the application and included their hex codes, RGB codes, and Tailwind utility class usage. The color scheme leans heavily into a dark, futuristic theme, with indigo and emerald/cyan serving as accents and glassmorphism for custom panels. I\'m verifying all the color values.\n\n\n**Refining Color Specifications**\n\nI\'m now refining the color specifications with precise hex and RGB values. I\'ve validated that `--color-slate-905` and `bg-[#0b0f19]` are identical in their effects, even though the RGB values are a little different. I\'m adding colors like `#161e31`, `#0f172a`, and standard Tailwind indigo and emerald shades. I\'m also preparing to structure all the data in a clear table, organizing them by role and context.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "Here is the color scheme representation of this web application styled in a tabular form. The app adopts an ambient, high-contrast, premium **deep-space dark theme** featuring translucent glassmorphism effects and radiant indigo/emerald accents:\n\n### Web Application Color Palette\n\n| Color Role | Aesthetic Context | Hex Code | RGB Equivalent | Tailwind CSS / CSS Variable Usage |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Primary Canvas** | Deep dark app backdrop | `#020617` <br> `#0b0f19` | `rgb(2, 6, 23)` <br> `rgb(11, 15, 25)` | `bg-slate-950` <br> `bg-[#0b0f19]` / `--color-slate-905` |\n| **Glassmorphic Surfaces** | Low-opacity glass panel cards | `#0f172a` | `rgb(15, 23, 42)` | `.glass-panel` base (`bg-[#0f172a]/30`) & `.glass-panel-heavy` |\n| **Muted Panels & Inputs** | Solid input card and sidebar blocks | `#0f172a` | `rgb(15, 23, 42)` | `bg-slate-900` / `bg-slate-900/60` |\n| **Borders & Dividers** | Structural borders and lines | `#161e31` <br> `#1e293b` | `rgb(22, 30, 49)` <br> `rgb(30, 41, 59)` | `--color-slate-850` / `border-slate-800` |\n| **Brand Primary Accent** | Primary actions, highlights, glows | `#4f46e5` <br> `#818cf8` | `rgb(79, 70, 229)` <br> `rgb(129, 140, 248)` | `bg-indigo-600` / `text-indigo-400` / `.glow-indigo` |\n| **Success / Diagnostics** | Action confirmation status & live glows | `#10b981` | `rgb(16, 185, 129)` | `text-emerald-400` / `.glow-emerald` / `.live-dot-ring` |\n| **High Density Text** | Most readable content, titles | `#f1f5f9` <br> `#e2e8f0` | `rgb(241, 245, 249)` <br> `rgb(226, 232, 240)` | `text-gray-100` <br> `text-gray-200` |\n| **Secondary Metadata** | Low-priority descriptions, labels | `#64748b` | `rgb(100, 116, 139)` | `text-slate-500` |\n\n### Key Stylistic Effects\n- **Backdrop Blur (`glass-panel`):** Combines soft translucent slate overlays (`bg-[#0f172a]/30`) with a `backdrop-blur-xl` and thin borders (`border-slate-850/40`) to present deep-layer hierarchical information clearly.\n- **Accented Ambient Glows:** Implements soft radial shadows under focal components via specific class definitions such as `glow-indigo` (`rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.15)`) to emphasize important panels without creating visual noise."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 5
      nanos: 763725977
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
