  user_input {
    user_response: "ok. we have a few tasks for you.\n\nfirst move from coloring and css of the app to using tailwindcss\nthe add a theme option. it should have system, light and dark.\nalso i dont like the current color scheme. use the following palette. or something similar:\n```\n## Academic Analytics Platform Palette\n\n| Role                        | Light Mode | Dark Mode |\n| --------------------------- | ---------- | --------- |\n| Background                  | `#F8FAFC`  | `#0F172A` |\n| Surface                     | `#FFFFFF`  | `#172033` |\n| Elevated Surface            | `#F1F5F9`  | `#1E293B` |\n| Border                      | `#CBD5E1`  | `#334155` |\n| Primary (Actions)           | `#2563EB`  | `#60A5FA` |\n| Secondary (Academic Accent) | `#14B8A6`  | `#2DD4BF` |\n| Success                     | `#22C55E`  | `#4ADE80` |\n| Warning                     | `#F59E0B`  | `#FBBF24` |\n| Error                       | `#EF4444`  | `#F87171` |\n| Info                        | `#38BDF8`  | `#7DD3FC` |\n| Primary Text                | `#0F172A`  | `#F8FAFC` |\n| Secondary Text              | `#334155`  | `#CBD5E1` |\n| Muted Text                  | `#64748B`  | `#94A3B8` |\n| Academic Gold (Optional)    | `#D4AF37`  | `#E6C75A` |\n\n### Chart Colors\n\n| Metric  | Light Mode | Dark Mode |\n| ------- | ---------- | --------- |\n| Chart 1 | `#2563EB`  | `#60A5FA` |\n| Chart 2 | `#14B8A6`  | `#2DD4BF` |\n| Chart 3 | `#F59E0B`  | `#FBBF24` |\n| Chart 4 | `#8B5CF6`  | `#A78BFA` |\n| Chart 5 | `#22C55E`  | `#4ADE80` |\n| Chart 6 | `#EC4899`  | `#F472B6` |\n\n### One-Line Summary\n\n| Theme     | Character                                               |\n| --------- | ------------------------------------------------------- |\n| **Light** | Clean, academic, approachable, paperwork-friendly       |\n| **Dark**  | Modern, professional, low-eye-strain, analytics-focused |\n\nThis palette will feel much more natural to **teachers, professors, TAs, department heads, and academic administrators** than the current indigo-glassmorphism dashboard aesthetic.\n```"
    items {
      text: "ok. we have a few tasks for you.\n\nfirst move from coloring and css of the app to using tailwindcss\nthe add a theme option. it should have system, light and dark.\nalso i dont like the current color scheme. use the following palette. or something similar:\n```\n## Academic Analytics Platform Palette\n\n| Role                        | Light Mode | Dark Mode |\n| --------------------------- | ---------- | --------- |\n| Background                  | `#F8FAFC`  | `#0F172A` |\n| Surface                     | `#FFFFFF`  | `#172033` |\n| Elevated Surface            | `#F1F5F9`  | `#1E293B` |\n| Border                      | `#CBD5E1`  | `#334155` |\n| Primary (Actions)           | `#2563EB`  | `#60A5FA` |\n| Secondary (Academic Accent) | `#14B8A6`  | `#2DD4BF` |\n| Success                     | `#22C55E`  | `#4ADE80` |\n| Warning                     | `#F59E0B`  | `#FBBF24` |\n| Error                       | `#EF4444`  | `#F87171` |\n| Info                        | `#38BDF8`  | `#7DD3FC` |\n| Primary Text                | `#0F172A`  | `#F8FAFC` |\n| Secondary Text              | `#334155`  | `#CBD5E1` |\n| Muted Text                  | `#64748B`  | `#94A3B8` |\n| Academic Gold (Optional)    | `#D4AF37`  | `#E6C75A` |\n\n### Chart Colors\n\n| Metric  | Light Mode | Dark Mode |\n| ------- | ---------- | --------- |\n| Chart 1 | `#2563EB`  | `#60A5FA` |\n| Chart 2 | `#14B8A6`  | `#2DD4BF` |\n| Chart 3 | `#F59E0B`  | `#FBBF24` |\n| Chart 4 | `#8B5CF6`  | `#A78BFA` |\n| Chart 5 | `#22C55E`  | `#4ADE80` |\n| Chart 6 | `#EC4899`  | `#F472B6` |\n\n### One-Line Summary\n\n| Theme     | Character                                               |\n| --------- | ------------------------------------------------------- |\n| **Light** | Clean, academic, approachable, paperwork-friendly       |\n| **Dark**  | Modern, professional, low-eye-strain, analytics-focused |\n\nThis palette will feel much more natural to **teachers, professors, TAs, department heads, and academic administrators** than the current indigo-glassmorphism dashboard aesthetic.\n```"
    }
  }
}
