    thinking: "**Analyzing Color Usage**\n\nI\'ve been digging into the app\'s CSS. I\'m seeing a heavy reliance on hardcoded indigo-style color values. There\'s a lot of `bg-indigo-500/10` and similar shades littering the code, along with hex codes like `#0c1222`. I need to figure out the rationale behind this approach and how to best manage it for maintainability.\n\n\n**Defining Theme Variables**\n\nI\'m now focusing on defining theme variables. It clicked \342\200\223 using Tailwind\'s theme customization to make things easier, and also make switching themes a breeze. I\'m exploring how to translate the provided palette into standard CSS variables within Tailwind\'s `@theme` directive (or just normal CSS variables). I\'m planning to make classes such as `bg-background`, `text-primary`, and `border-border`. This should give us the desired flexibility for system, light, and dark modes. I am focused on organizing these to be very useful and well defined.\n\n\n**Defining CSS Variables**\n\nI\'m now focusing on mapping the provided color palette to CSS custom properties. It seems like the best approach. I plan to define variables like `--color-warning-light`, `--color-error-dark`, and similar for the given colors. I\'m exploring the Tailwind version to ensure compatibility and integration. I plan to put all of these variables in the `:root` and `.dark` selectors within `index.css` for easy access and theming. My next step will be mapping these variables to the new Tailwind classes.\n\n\n**Confirming Tailwind Compatibility**\n\nI\'ve confirmed that this project uses Tailwind v4 with the `@import \"tailwindcss\";` and `@theme { ... }` syntax. Now, I will define the new theme colors as CSS custom properties with their light and dark mode variations. I\'m focusing on perfectly mapping the provided light and dark mode color schemes into these properties for seamless integration.\n\n```\nI\'m now implementing the plan, creating the CSS custom properties for light and dark modes within `:root` and `.dark` selectors. I\'m carefully transferring the hex codes from the provided style definitions to ensure accurate color representation. I think it is important to take charts into account. My next step will be to connect these variables to the Tailwind utility classes.\n```\n\n"
