e styling. I\'ve rethemed the `FileCheck2` icon to use `text-primary` when active and `text-muted-text` when inactive for better visual clarity. I\'ve also rethemed the `FileCheck2` icon. The text spans within the sidebar have been rethemed to use consistent muted text. Finally, I\'ve rethemed the context menu background, borders, and text to match the selected theme.\n\n\n**Integrating Theme Switcher**\n\nI\'m now incorporating a theme switcher segmented control into the sidebar\'s footer panel. I\'m focusing on the visual integration and ensuring it complements the existing account settings. My goal is for a seamless and intuitive user experience.\n\n\n**Designing Theme Switcher Styling**\n\nI\'m now focusing on styling a theme switcher segmented control for the sidebar\'s footer panel, specifically the \"Elena Rostova\" section. I\'m aiming for a visually appealing and cohesive look that will fit right inside this footer. I\'ve designed a layout that should look right, now, I just have to integrate it, with good styling.\n\n\n**Implementing Theme Switcher Buttons**\n\nI\'ve integrated the theme switcher buttons within the sidebar footer, using `Sun`, `Moon`, and `Monitor` icons for light, dark, and system themes. I\'ve used `bg-elevated`, `bg-surface`, `text-primary`, and `text-muted-text` for a seamless integration. I\'ve also implemented the transition effects, and now, it looks incredible!\n\n\n"
